<h2>Report metrics for another product</h2>

<p>If you have permission to report for multiple products, you can submit metrics on behalf of other products you're responsible for.</p>

<h3>When to report for another product</h3>
<p>You might need to report for another product if:</p>
<ul>
    <li>You're a product owner for multiple products</li>
    <li>You're covering for a colleague</li>
    <li>You have delegated reporting responsibilities</li>
    <li>You're part of a team that manages multiple products</li>
</ul>

<h3>Finding the product</h3>
<ol>
    <li>Navigate to <strong>Reporting → Operational reporting</strong></li>
    <li>Use the search or filters to find the product</li>
    <li>Click on the product name</li>
    <li>You'll see the same submission interface as for your own products</li>
</ol>

<h3>Submitting metrics</h3>
<p>The process is the same as submitting for your own product:</p>
<ol>
    <li>Enter the metric values</li>
    <li>Review your entries</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Submit</strong></li>
</ol>
<p>The system will record that you submitted on behalf of that product.</p>

<h3>Permissions</h3>
<p>You can only report for products where you have:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Product owner permissions</li>
    <li>Delegated reporting access</li>
    <li>Team member access with reporting rights</li>
</ul>
<p>If you can't see a product, you may not have the required permissions.</p>

<h3>Viewing history for other products</h3>
<p>You can view the reporting history for products you have access to:</p>
<ol>
    <li>Go to the product's page</li>
    <li>Click <strong>View History</strong></li>
    <li>See all past submissions</li>
</ol>

<h3>Best practices</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Confirm you have the correct data before submitting</li>
    <li>Check with the product owner if you're unsure about values</li>
    <li>Document any assumptions or notes</li>
    <li>Submit on time to avoid late status</li>
    <li>Let the product owner know you've submitted on their behalf</li>
</ul>

<h3>Multiple products</h3>
<p>If you manage multiple products:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Use the product list to see all products requiring submission</li>
    <li>Filter or search to find specific products</li>
    <li>Submit for each product separately</li>
    <li>Check the status of all your products regularly</li>
</ul>

<h3>Getting help</h3>
<p>If you need to report for a product but don't have access:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Contact the product owner</li>
    <li>Request access from your business area administrator</li>
    <li>Check if permissions need to be updated</li>
</ul>

